[Comentario en Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_GainSight.sql:82 por @Copilot]: The variable @environment is referenced but not declared in this scope. The function fn_util_get_env() returns the environment value, but it's not being called or assigned to @environment variable.
```suggestion

DECLARE @environment NVARCHAR(100);
SET @environment = dbo.fn_util_get_env();
```
[Comentario en Core/API Layer/ProjectSight.WebAPI/Controllers/v1/SyncController.cs:289 por @Copilot]: The hardcoded "mobile" region string should be defined as a constant or retrieved from configuration to maintain consistency and avoid magic strings.
```suggestion
                var context = gainsight.GenerateGlobalContext(portfolioDB, RequestedBy, MobileRegion);
```
[Comentario en Core/Common/Components/Gainsight/GainsightSettings.cs:56 por @Copilot]: The default value "Unknown" should be defined as a constant to ensure consistency across the codebase and make it easier to maintain.
```suggestion
            Region = parameters?.Region ?? DEFAULT_REGION;  
```
[Comentario en Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_GainSight.sql:64 por @Copilot]: `fn_util_get_env` declares `@environment` but returns `@Environment`. On case-sensitive collations this will raise "Must declare the scalar variable" and break the update script. Return the declared variable (`@environment`).
[Comentario en Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_GainSight.sql:61 por @Copilot]: The environment mapping in `fn_util_get_env` appears to have diverged from `update_db_ignition_template.sql` (which includes `WHEN 'projectsight-labs' THEN 'labs'`). If this runs in the labs environment it will fall through to `other`, producing the wrong Region/Data_Center.
[Comentario en Core/Common/Components/Gainsight/GainsightSettings.cs:56 por @Copilot]: `JsonConvert.DeserializeObject` will throw if `service.ParametersJson` is an empty/whitespace string (common for newly created ExternalService rows). Consider normalizing with `string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(service?.ParametersJson) ? "{}" : service.ParametersJson` before deserializing so Gainsight settings retrieval can’t fail due to blank JSON.
[Comentario en Core/Common/Components/Gainsight/GainsightSettings.cs:17 por @Copilot]: `Region` is a new public property but (a) it has no XML doc like the other public settings properties, and (b) it’s publicly settable even though it’s intended to be derived from ExternalService configuration. Consider adding a `<summary>` and making it `get; private set;` (or `get;`) to prevent accidental mutation after construction.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/SyncSystem.cs:84 por @Copilot]: This call now populates the new `Data_Center` global-context field with the literal string "mobile". Given the PR’s goal is to disambiguate shared users/accounts across actual data centers (EU/UK/AU/NA), this looks like it will send incorrect region data for mobile telemetry. Prefer passing the configured Gainsight region (from ExternalService.ParametersJson / `GainsightSettings.Region`) instead of a placeholder.
[Comentario en Core/SQL/delta_procs.sql:22 por @Copilot]: `delta_procs.sql` is a generated file and this hunk only changes machine-local `sqlpackage.exe` path/version metadata (no corresponding `base_procs.sql` changes in this PR). Per `docs/ai/BACKEND_CONVENTIONS.md:92`, generated `delta_procs.sql` should not be edited/committed unless it reflects actual proc diffs—please revert this header-only churn to avoid embedding developer-specific paths in the repo.
[Comentario en Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_GainSight.sql:64 por @rroesler]: Fixed and script updated from latest template
[Comentario en Core/Common/Components/Gainsight/GainsightSettings.cs:56 por @rroesler]: These are the same.  Unknown replace with GainsightSettings.UNKNOWN
[Comentario en Core/Common/Components/Gainsight/GainsightSettings.cs:56 por @rroesler]: Added to GainsightSettings
[Comentario en Core/API Layer/ProjectSight.WebAPI/Controllers/v1/SyncController.cs:289 por @rroesler]: Added to GaightsightSettings
[Comentario en Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_GainSight.sql:61 por @rroesler]: Fixed I believe,
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/SyncSystem.cs:84 por @rroesler]: Fixed .. but also Copilot is incorrect.   The region is passed from configuration BUT the mobile does not actualually care what the region string is.  Only WebUI did.    So we pass a fake string just for the API contract
[Comentario en Core/SQL/delta_procs.sql:23 por @Copilot]: `delta_procs.sql` is a generated artifact; this change updates machine-specific `sqlpackage.exe` path/version info (e.g., `C:\Users\...`) without any corresponding `base_procs.sql` change. Per `docs/ai/BACKEND_CONVENTIONS.md` (§3: SQL & Data Access), this file should only be regenerated/committed when the proc delta actually changes—otherwise it creates noisy diffs and bakes local-environment details into source control. Please revert this delta_procs change (or regenerate it as part of an intentional proc update).
[Comentario en Core/SQL/delta_procs.sql:22 por @rroesler]: Interesting.  For me this delta-procs will have to get recompiled again on yet another merge where is might make a difference.   But I will keep this in mind for the future.

